Ghana â€™s parliament approved loans to
finance the purchase of five aircraft for the armed forces, the
Graphic reported.  The  Brazilian Development Bank  will lend $105.4 million for
the purchase of an Ember 190, related logistics and construction
of a hangar, the Accra-based newspaper said, citing Ghanaian
Minister of Defense  Joseph Smith .  Deutsche Bank S.A.E.  will provide a 60 million-euro ($85.5
million) loan for the acquisition of two CASA 295 military
transport aircrafts, the Graphic said. Another loan of 11.8
million euros from  Fidelity Bank Ltd.  of  Ghana  will help fund
the purchase of two DA42 MPP Guardian Surveillance aircrafts, it
said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
